latestPosts.caption:
In Rajiv Joseph’s Guards at the Taj, Humayun and Babur stand guard at the gates of the Taj Mahal the night before its unveiling. Humayun prides himself in being a man of honour and duty, while Babur is a contrasting representation of freedom and life. Though they are polar opposites, their friendship has stood the test of time. But can it continue to do so with changing political landscape? In this dark comedy drama, we explore notions of loyalty, brotherhood and free will.

Show details: 

🗓: 30th November, 1st, 7th, and 8th December
📍: @jeffgoldbergstudio 
⏳️: 7.30 p.m. 

To get your tickets, visit BookMyShow! 
See you soon 🤙🏼

[Mumbai, Acting, Theatre, Hindi Play, Weekends in Mumbai]
